						"title": "The State of DDoS Threats: Q4 2023 Report",
						"subtitle": null,
						"copy": "In times of economic uncertainty and geopolitical conflict, cyber attack activity heightens. Organizations must remain vigilant and have solid continuity plans in place – DDoS attacks can cause critical services, applications, and infrastructure to go down. Downtime can ultimately damage your organization's revenue, reputation, and productivity.\n\nBy analyzing traffic patterns across our global network, we've identified emerging DDoS threats and tracked known DDoS trends over time. By understanding these threats early, your organization can prevent attacks from disrupting business operations.\n\nRead the __Q4 2023 DDoS Threat Landscape Report__ to learn more about:\n\n- DDoS trends for the year 2023\n- DDoS attacks during the Israel-Hamas war, the Taiwan general election season and after COP28 \n- The holiday season DDoS grinch\n- Best practices to deal with sophisticated network and application layer DDoS attacks",
